In this newsletter: Friday-Sunday May 2-4, M/S Silja Symphony MONDAY BAR: THE GRAND 2025 CRUISE (no 62) • 2 night cruise to Helsinki, Finland (4o hrs) • Cabin booking opens Friday October 25, 10.00 • 10 headline djs presented so far. The rest of the lineup will be announced weekly until Christmas Friday Nov 29 - POSTPONED! POSTPONED: MONDAY BAR MEATMARKET • New date: Saturday March 15 • Refund of tickets at C.U.M. or keep them until next event MONDAY BAR: THE 2024 CRUISE, Sept 20-22 • 500 amazing pictures by Timo Torvikoski Dear Monday Bar family, The lineup for the the next cruise, Monday Bar: The Grand 2025 Cruise (May 2-4) is slowly shaping up. We have so far presented 10 headliners on our social media and homepage, and will continue to present the rest weekly until Christmas. A total of 50+ international and local djs. The cruise booking is officially open from Friday October 25, at 10.00. And the November 29 event at Slakthuset that was announced earlier in the cruise program has been postponed until Saturday March 15. For those of you who have already purchased tickets, you can get a cash refund at C.U.M. Clubwear or save them until March 15. We’re sorry for the inconvenience. Monday Bar crew 🥰 THE GRAND 2025 CRUISE - ON A MAJESTIC SHIP! With only one planned cruise each year there are more people wanting to go than there is enough space on one regular ship. So we asked Tallink-Silja if we could once again book the most majestic cruise ship in their fleet, M/S SILJA SYMPHONY, a huge vessel with room for almost 3000 passengers. If you joined our 20th anniversary cruise in 2012 you know what we’re talking about. Among other attractions, this unique ship has a 150 meter long promenade street in the middle that can be turned into a dance floor. Then of course, there are several other great floors onboard. This is what it's all about.. the official after-movie from 2012 at M/S Silja Symphony: Monday Bar 20th anniversary Cruise 2012 <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=21bA6A5dpy0> LINEUP Most of the lineup will be presented in the following weeks on Facebook and our homepage with over 50 international and local djs in trance, hardstyle, psy trance, techno, hardcore, etc. We will mix the dance floors with different music styles, so that most music styles will be represented everywhere. On our main floor, one dj per style will play each night, Friday and Saturday. Weekly lineup updates at: https://www.mondaybar.com BOOKING CABINS / TICKETS Booking online and by phone will be available starting Friday October 25. To join this cruise you need to book a cabin. There are cabins for 2-4 people that you can share with your friends. You only pay for your cabin, no other cost will be added apart from the drinks and food that you consume on board and the money spent on duty free goods. All entertainment on board is included in the cabin price. It’s possible to postpone payment with at least 2 weeks after the original booking has been made. It is also possible to engage in a long payment plan through KLARNA credit. BOOKING ONLINE & BY PHONE Starting Friday October 25, 10.00 Online booking link <https://www.tallinksilja.se/monday-bar> Tallink-Silja booking office: +46 (0)8-666 33 33 (extra charge) Booking reference: MBAR All booking info, prices, etc at the cruise homepage <https://www.mondaybar.com?ss_source=sscampaigns&ss_campaign_id=6719244892d9aa61be0da843&ss_email_id=67192f1892d9aa61be0f7ee3&ss_campaign_name=%E2%9A%93%EF%B8%8F+Monday+Bar+Newsletter+week+43+%F0%9F%9B%B3&ss_campaign_sent_date=2024-10-23T17%3A15%3A16Z> . MONDAY BAR - THE GRAND 2025 CRUISE (no 62) Friday-Sunday, May 2-4 (40 hr cruise) M/S Silja Symphony Stockholm-Helsinki-Stockholm Cruise times Departure, Stockholm Tallink-Silja ferry terminal, Värtahamnen Friday, May 2, 16:45 (4:45 PM), local Swedish time Arrival, Helsinki Olympia ferry terminal Saturday, May 3, 10:30 (10.30 AM), local Finnish time (+1 hour) Departure, Helsinki Olympia ferry terminal Saturday, May 3, 17:00 